-- Saudi's Riyad Bank recommends H2 2014 dividend of 35 halalas
-- By Tom Arnold
-- Tue Dec 30, 2014 01:43AM EST
-- None



DUBAI, Dec 30 (Reuters) - The board of Saudi Arabia's Riyad Bank <1010.SE>, the kingdom's third-largest listed bank by assets, said on Tuesday that it was recommending a dividend of 35 halalas per share for the second half of 2014.

That compares with a dividend of 80 halalas for the second half of 2013. [ID:nL6N0KH0EK]